Properties Of SortedSet Interface :

1) SortedSet can not have null element .
   if you try to insert null element ,
   it gives NullpointerException run time

2)As sortedset is  a set ,duplicate elements are not allowed

3)SortedSet element are sorted according to supplied comparator.
if you don't mention any comparator while creating a SortedSet,
element will be placed in ascending order

4)Inserted element must be of comparable type and they must be
mutually comparable.

5)You can retrive first element and last elements of sortedSet. you
cant't access sortedSet elements randomly i.e Random access is denied

6) Sortedset  returned by headSet(),tailSet() and subSet() are just view of
the original set . So, changes in the returned set are reflected in the original set and vice versa.






















